## Project Documentation Structure

All project documentation is stored within the `docs/` directory. Standard subdirectories include:
*   `docs/api/`
*   `docs/design/`
*   `docs/logs/`
*   `docs/strategy/`
*   `docs/technical/` (including `RELEASE_PLAN.md`)
*   `docs/user-stories/` (including `backlog/` and `sprint-X/`)

Design assets for user stories are located in `docs/user-stories/{sprint}/{user-story}/design/`.
User stories should be stored in `stories/` (this seems to conflict with `docs/user-stories/`, clarify which is primary).
Release plans should be stored in the `releases/` directory as YAML files (this also seems to conflict with `docs/technical/RELEASE_PLAN.md`).

## Cursor Rules Symlinking

To maintain consistency across projects, this `.cursor/rules` directory should be symlinked to the project root directory for all new projects. The preferred method is `ln -s .cursor/rules project-root/.cursor-rules-symlink` (or similar, actual command might vary by OS/setup - `mklink /D` on Windows in elevated prompt if `ln -s` fails). The goal is a consistent way to access these rules.

